node.description:
__Alma Mater:__ Toyo University

__[Website](https://www.yukihayashi.net/)__ | __[Twitter](https://twitter.com/hayayu1231)__

__Introduction:__
Yuuki Hayashi is a Japanese composer and arranger affiliated with Legendoor, who used to be a rhythmic gymnast

__Biography:__
His history in music began in university when he started creating music pieces for rhythmic gymnasts as a hobby for 5000 yen a piece. When he started getting requests from other universities for his music, his interest in music producing grew. After graduation, he was taught music for 6 months by a rhythmic gymnastics music producer, and now, he handles music for various sports. He also arranges music for dance, athletic competitions, companies, independent movies and recently, TV dramas and anime.

(Source: MyAnimeList, edited)

[Wiki (jp)](https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/東堂いづみ) | [Wiki (en)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Izumi_Todo)

Izumi Toudou is a collective pseudonym for [Toei Animation](https://anilist.co/studio/18/)'s staff.

__[Profile (Legendoor)](http://www.legendoor.com/artist/%E6%A9%98%E9%BA%BB%E7%BE%8E)__ | __[Twitter](https://twitter.com/AsamiTachibana)__ | __[Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/achaamiii/)__ | __[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/user/caffemocha0428)__

A Japanese pianist, composer and arranger affiliated with Legendoor.

[Twitter](https://twitter.com/i/user/1319638475969183744)

Director and storyboard artist affiliated with [Toei Animation](https://anilist.co/studio/18/Toei-Animation).

Director formerly affiliated with [Toei Animation](https://anilist.co/studio/18). Currently affiliated with studio maf.

Influenced by [Yasunori Koyama](https://anilist.co/staff/276622) and [Megumi Ishitani](https://anilist.co/staff/141539).

His favorite animators are [Tetsuya Takeuchi](https://anilist.co/staff/101404), [Takahiro Kishida](https://anilist.co/staff/101403) and [Katsuhiko Kitada](https://anilist.co/staff/127730).

Watching [FLCL](https://anilist.co/anime/227) in high school, he fell in love with animation and wanted to become a director. [Toshiyuki Tsuru](https://anilist.co/staff/106123)'s episodes and openings of [Naruto](https://anilist.co/anime/20) were the turning point for him, and he started in the animation industry as an assistant director at Toei.

He works mainly on [ONE PIECE](https://anilist.co/anime/21) and pays a lot of attention to lighting and animation. As an animator, he often corrects timing and animates parts of his episodes.

[Twitter](https://twitter.com/i/user/155508177)

Photography Director affiliated with Toei Animation.
